  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (inconsistent requirements)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: package binds two requirements whose acceptance thresholds for relative hemolysis index are mutually exclusive — REQ-HEM-01 mandates RH < 1.0 (strict less-than) while REQ-HEM-02 mandates RH ≤ 1.0 AND RH ≥ 1.0 simultaneously as the passing band, permitting the predicate-equivalent value that REQ-HEM-01 forbids.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/hem-01-strict-less-than",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou1-cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
