    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out per MRL 2 requirements. Maximum predicted RH = 0.91 across all five operating points, satisfying the RH < 1.0 acceptance criterion of REQ-HEM-01. The credibility assessment team concludes the CFD model is sufficiently credible for the CPB COU to support regulatory submission. Note: REQ-HEM-02 was incorporated during late-stage review to accommodate measurement uncertainty and permits RH = 1.0 as conforming — this contradicts the strict inequality mandated by REQ-HEM-01, but since all results are below 0.95 the contradiction was not flagged during review.",
